==主要原则==
沙斐仪学派规定了五个权威的[[伊斯兰教法|教法]]来源。按照等级划分的顺序，首先依靠的是[[古兰经|古兰经]]，其次是[[圣训|圣训]]；<ref name=hmr/><ref name=philtar/>当古兰经和圣训解释模棱两可时，沙斐仪学派则从“[[公议|公议]]”（先知[[穆罕默德|穆罕默德]][[萨哈巴|同伴]]们的一致意见）中寻求教法指导；<ref>Syafiq Hasyim (2005), Understanding Women in Islam: An Indonesian Perspective, Equinox, ISBN 978-9793780191, pp. 75-77</ref> 如果没有一致意见，则依据“[[伊智提哈德|伊智提哈德]]”（穆罕默德同伴的个人意见）；最后再依靠[[类比|类比]]。<ref name="hmr">Hisham M. Ramadan (2006), Understanding Islamic Law: From Classical to Contemporary, Rowman Altamira, ISBN 978-0759109919, pp. 27-28</ref>

沙斐仪学派否认“[[伊斯提哈桑|伊斯提哈桑]]”（又译“优选”，在有更强的证据时放弃以前判例作出的新裁决）和“[[伊斯提斯拉赫|伊斯提斯拉赫]]”（又译“公益”，在公共利益基础上进行的判决）这两个原则的权威性，尽管他们被其他教法学派承认。<ref name=oup1>[http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t125/e1139 Istislah] {{Wayback|url=http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t125/e1139 |date=20150607063556 }} The Oxford Dictionary of Islam, Oxford University Press</ref><ref name=oup2>[http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t125/e1136 Istihsan] {{Wayback|url=http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t125/e1136 |date=20150607063656 }} The Oxford Dictionary of Islam, Oxford University Press</ref>“优选”和“公益”这两个原则没有古兰经或圣训的原文作为基础，只是伊斯兰教法学家们为了推广伊斯兰教的所作的理解。<ref>Lloyd Ridgeon (2003), Major World Religions: From Their Origins To The Present, Routledge, ISBN 978-0415297967, pp. 259-262</ref>沙斐仪学派认为这两个原则是依靠的是人类的意见，可能产生[[政治腐败|腐败]]现象或会随着政治环境发生改变，因此拒绝承认其作为法学来源。<ref name=oup1/><ref name=oup2/>

==分布==
[[穆斯林世界|穆斯林世界]]中，沙斐仪学派主要通行于下述地区：<ref name=unc1>[http://veil.unc.edu/religions/islam/law/ Jurisprudence and Law - Islam] {{Wayback|url=http://veil.unc.edu/religions/islam/law/ |date=20190629031815 }} Reorienting the Veil, University of North Carolina (2009)</ref>
*[[非洲|非洲]]：[[吉布提|吉布提]]，[[索马里|索马里]]，[[埃塞俄比亚|埃塞俄比亚]]，[[埃及|埃及]]东部，以及[[东非|东非]]{{link-en|印度洋沿岸地区|Swahili coast}}。<ref>[http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/222247.pdf UNION OF THE COMOROS 2013 INTERNATIONAL RELIGIOUS FREEDOM REPORT] {{Wayback|url=http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/222247.pdf |date=20150924123010 }} U.S. State Department (2014), Quote: "The law provides sanctions for any religious practice other than the Sunni Shafi’i doctrine of Islam and for prosecution of converts from Islam, and bans proselytizing for any religion except Islam."</ref>
*[[中东|中东]]： [[也门|也门]]，[[库尔德斯坦|库尔德斯坦]]，[[以色列|以色列]]，[[黎巴嫩|黎巴嫩]]，[[约旦|约旦]]部分地区，[[巴勒斯坦|巴勒斯坦]]，以及[[沙特阿拉伯|沙特阿拉伯]]部分地区。
*[[高加索|高加索]]：[[阿塞拜疆|阿塞拜疆]]部分地区<ref>[http://www.css.ethz.ch/publications/pdfs/CAD-44-2-4.pdf Islam in Azerbaijan (Historical Background)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.css.ethz.ch/publications/pdfs/CAD-44-2-4.pdf |date=20150123200453 }}, Altay Goyushov, CAUCASUS ANALYTICAL DIGEST No. 44, 20 November 2012</ref>。
*[[南亚|南亚]]和[[东南亚|东南亚]]：[[印度尼西亚|印度尼西亚]]，[[马来西亚|马来西亚]]，[[马尔代夫|马尔代夫]]，[[斯里兰卡|斯里兰卡]]，[[印度|印度]]西海岸，[[新加坡|新加坡]]，[[缅甸|缅甸]]，[[泰国|泰国]]，[[文莱|文莱]]，以及[[菲律宾|菲律宾]]南部地区。其中，伊斯兰教逊尼派沙斐仪学派是文莱和马来西亚的[[官方宗教|官方宗教]]。<ref name=cia>{{cite journal | url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bx.html | title=Brunei | publisher=[[CIA_World_Factbook|CIA World Factbook]] | year=2011 | accessdate=13 January 2011 | ref=harv | journal= | archive-date=2015-07-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721102115/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bx.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="malaysianbar.org.my">{{Cite web |url=http://www.malaysianbar.org.my/press_statements/press_statement_malaysia_a_secular_state.html |title=存档副本 |access-date=2015-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228154440/http://www.malaysianbar.org.my/press_statements/press_statement_malaysia_a_secular_state.html |archive-date=2018-12-28 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="Wu & Hickling, p. 35">Wu & Hickling, p. 35.</ref>

==主要观点==
不同穆斯林社区实行[[伊斯兰教法|伊斯兰教法]]的严格程度有所差异，部分社区只实行教法的部分方面，如[[婚姻|婚姻]]、[[继承|继承]]等。<ref name=tjmas>[http://www.cfr.org/religion/islam-governing-under-sharia/p8034 Islam: Governing under Sharia] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cfr.org/religion/islam-governing-under-sharia/p8034 |date=20181226012000 }} Toni Johnson and Mohammed Aly Sergie, Council on Foreign Relations (2013)</ref><ref>Amanat & Griffel (2007), SHARI’A: ISLAMIC LAW IN THE CONTEMPORARY CONTEXT, Stanford University Press, ISBN 978-0804756396</ref><ref name=rightto>{{cite web|title=I have a right to|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/people/features/ihavearightto/four_b/casestudy_art07.shtml|publisher=BBC World Service|accessdate=24 February 2013|archive-date=2018-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224211431/http://www.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/people/features/ihavearightto/four_b/casestudy_art07.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>下述为沙斐仪派伊斯兰教法的观点。
===叛教===
伊斯兰教法学的各个学派都认为[[叛教_(伊斯蘭教)|叛教]]是一种罪行。沙斐仪学派对于叛教者首先给予三天的时间等待其悔改<ref>Mohamed El-Awa (1993), Punishment in Islamic Law, American Trust Publications, ISBN 978-0892591428, pp 1-68</ref><ref name=fgriffel>Frank Griffel (2001), Toleration and exclusion: al-Shafi ‘i and al-Ghazali on the treatment of apostates, Bulletin of the School of Oriental and African Studies, 64(03): 339-354</ref><ref name=dforte>David Forte, [http://www.cepos.eu/pdf/revista%20de%20stiinte%20politice%20nr%2029.pdf Islam’s Trajectory] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cepos.eu/pdf/revista%20de%20stiinte%20politice%20nr%2029.pdf |date=20140903101606 }}, Revue des Sciences Politiques, No. 29 (2011), pages 92-101</ref>，若拒不悔改，传统的惩罚措施是处以[[死刑|死刑]]，无论是男性或女性。<ref name=petersdevries>Peters & De Vries (1976), [http://www.jstor.org/stable/1570336 Apostasy in Islam] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/1570336 |date=20160312104058 }}, Die Welt des Islams, Vol. 17, Issue 1/4, pp 1-25</ref><ref name=dforte/>另外叛教者还要负民事责任，其财产要被没收并分发给穆斯林亲属，其[[婚姻|婚姻]]宣布无效，子女交由国家监护。<ref name=petersdevries/>

===亵渎===
沙斐仪派认为[[亵渎|亵渎]]是指侮辱或贬低[[安拉|安拉]]、[[穆罕默德|穆罕默德]]或与伊斯兰教相关其他事物的行为<ref>Aḥmad ibn Luʼluʼ Ibn al-Naqīb (Trans: Noah Ha Mim Keller, 1997), The Reliance of the Traveller, ISBN 978-0915957729</ref>，而亵渎和叛教是两种罪名。对于亵渎者，沙斐仪学派也给予悔改的机会，拒不悔改者传统上处以死刑，无论男性或女性。<ref name=lw>L Wiederhold L, Blasphemy against the Prophet Muhammad and his companions (sabb al-rasul, sabb al-sahabah) : The introduction of the topic into Shafi'i legal literature, Jrnl of Sem Studies, Oxford University Press, 42(1), pp. 39-70</ref><ref>P Smith (2003), Speak No Evil: Apostasy, Blasphemy and Heresy in Malaysian Syariah Law, UC Davis Journal Int'l Law & Policy, 10, pp. 357-373;
*F Griffel (2001), Toleration and exclusion: al-Shafi ‘i and al-Ghazali on the treatment of apostates, Bulletin of the School of Oriental and African Studies, 64(3), pp. 339-354</ref>

===石刑===
对于[[通奸|通奸]]或[[同性恋|同性恋]]等伊斯兰教所禁止的性行为，沙斐仪学派认为应当处以[[石刑|石刑]]。如果被指控者未婚，则可改为公开[[鞭刑|鞭刑]]。<ref name="es8">Elyse Semerdjian (2008), "Off the Straight Path": Illicit Sex, Law, and Community in Ottoman Aleppo, Syracuse University Press, ISBN 978-0815631736, pp. 22-23</ref>沙斐仪学派认可自我陈述、四个男性目击证人的证词（不接受女性的证词）以及怀孕（有时会有争议）为非法性行为的证据。<ref>Elyse Semerdjian (2008), "Off the Straight Path": Illicit Sex, Law, and Community in Ottoman Aleppo, Syracuse University Press, ISBN 978-0815631736, p. 25</ref>

===彩礼===
与其他学派不同，沙斐仪学派没有规定结婚时穆斯林男方家庭必须付给女方的[[彩礼|彩礼]]金额的最低值。<ref name="kali5657">K Ali (2010), Marriage and Slavery in Early Islam, Harvard University Press, ISBN 978-0674050594, pp. 56-57</ref>

===其他观点===
*与其他逊尼派伊斯兰教法学学派一样，沙斐仪派也规定最小的结婚年龄为：男性12岁，女性9岁。而成年的年龄是：男性18岁，女性17岁，成年之后可独自订立婚约。[[监护人|监护人]]有权安排[[未成年人|未成年人]]的婚姻。<ref>Lynn Welchman (2000), Beyond the Code: Muslim Family Law and the Shariʼa Judiciary, Brill, ISBN 978-9041188595, pp. 108-110</ref>
*传统的沙斐仪学派认为，男方有权和女方[[离婚|离婚]]，但女方不能首先向男方提出离婚。<ref>K Ali (2010), Marriage and Slavery in Early Islam, Harvard University Press, ISBN 978-0674050594, pp. 178-179</ref>
*其他教法学派禁止下[[国际象棋|国际象棋]]，而沙斐仪学派只是不提倡。<ref>The Word of Islam - Page 102, John Alden Williams - 1994</ref>
*沙斐仪派禁止[[音乐|音乐]]、[[歌唱|歌唱]]与[[舞蹈|舞蹈]]，这与其他学派的观点相似<ref name="lakhmr">L. Ali Khan and Hisham M. Ramadan (2011), Contemporary Ijtihad: Limits and Controversies, Oxford University Press, ISBN 978-0748641284, pp. 72-75</ref><ref>M Cook (2010), Commanding Right and Forbidding Wrong in Islamic Thought, Cambridge University Press, ISBN 978-0521130936, pp. 91-103, 145-182</ref>，并且认为所有的乐器都应当被摧毁。<ref>MA Cook (2003), Forbidding Wrong in Islam: An Introduction, Cambridge University Press, ISBN 978-0521536028, pp. 31-42, 60-68, 104-129</ref>
*沙斐仪派学者禁止对任何有生命的物体进行描绘、绘画。<ref>Thomas W. Arnold (2004), Painting in Islam: A Study of the Place of Pictorial Art in Muslim Culture, Gorgias Press, ISBN 978-1593331214, p. 9</ref><ref>Zaky Hassan (1944), The attitude of Islam towards painting, Bulletin of the Faculty ofArts (Cairo University), Vol. 7, pp. 1-15</ref><ref>Isa Salman (1969), Islam and figurative arts, Sumer, Vol. 25, pp. 59-96</ref>
*历史上曾有沙斐仪学派的文献批准过[[女性生殖器切割|女性割礼]]，而沙斐仪学派的创始人认为男性和女性都有接受[[割礼|割礼]]的义务。<ref>Anne Meneley (1996), Tournaments of Value: Sociability and Hierarchy in a Yemeni Town, University of Toronto Press, ISBN 978-0802078681, p. 84, footnote 8</ref><ref>
*[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=xek6yZPAQjAC&pg=PA436&dq= The Different Aspects of Islamic Culture] p 436, Abdelwahab Bouhdiba, Muḥammad Maʻrūf al- Dawālībī - 1998
*[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=QT3Tq6FfG0cC&pg=PA129&dq= Self-Determination and Women's Rights in Muslim Societies] - Page 129, Chitra Raghavan, James P. Levine - 2012</ref>
*沙斐仪学派禁止剃须，而其他学派只是不提倡。<ref>Reliance of the Traveller - Page 58, Nuh Mim Keller - 1994</ref>

